Iberdrola, FCC, Portugal Telecom: Iberian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-05-27T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/iberdrola-fcc-portugal-telecom-iberian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  slid 0.1 percent to 10,203.2 in
Madrid. Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  dropped 0.5 percent to 7,631.08.  Spanish stocks:  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  : Moody’s Investors Service said it
changed the rating outlook for the senior unsecured A3 ratings
of Iberdrola, its guaranteed subsidiaries and Scottish Power
Ltd. and its subsidiaries to stable from negative. The shares
climbed 0.3 percent to 6.05 euros.  Fomento de Construcciones & Contratas SA (FCC SM): Eurocis
SA and Larranza XXI SL pledged to keep its stake in B-1998 SL,
FCC’s biggest shareholder, until at least the end of 2016, the
Spanish company said in an e-mailed statement. The shares fell
0.7 percent to 20.73 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Portugal Telecom SGPS SA (PTC)  : Portugal’s biggest phone
company’s stake in Oi SA, which will combine the units of
Telemar Participacoes SA, may be higher than 21.5 percent, Chief
Executive Officer Zeinal Bava said in a conference call with
analysts. The company expects  capital spending  in Portugal this
year to be “in line” with 2010. The shares advanced 0.5
percent to 8.66 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net . 